docs.abstract: With the coronavirus exploding, trying to trace the contacts of every positive case has become unrealistic in Florida, especially among elusive partygoers.
docs.snippet: With the coronavirus exploding, trying to trace the contacts of every positive case has become unrealistic in Florida, especially among elusive partygoers.
docs.lead_paragraph: MIAMI — Miami’s flashy nightclubs closed in March, but the parties have raged on in the waterfront manse tucked in the lush residential neighborhood of Belle Meade Island. Revelers arrive in sports cars and ride-shares several nights a week, say neighbors who have spied professional bouncers at the door and bought earplugs to try to sleep through the thumping dance beats.

headline.main: As the Virus Surged, Florida Partied. Tracking the Revelers Has Been Tough.
headline.print_headline: Virus Finds a Feast at House Parties in Florida

docs.abstract: The body of John Lewis crossed the Edmund Pettus Bridge on Sunday, more than a half century after he helped change American history there.
docs.snippet: The body of John Lewis crossed the Edmund Pettus Bridge on Sunday, more than a half century after he helped change American history there.
docs.lead_paragraph: SELMA, Ala. — On a different Sunday in Selma, this one more than five decades ago, John Lewis was a 25-year-old activist wearing a long tan coat and carrying a backpack, helping to marshal hundreds of demonstrators across the Edmund Pettus Bridge. They were bombarded by clouds of tear gas and swarmed by state troopers wielding clubs, one of which fractured Mr. Lewis’s skull.

headline.main: Selma Helped Define John Lewis’s Life. In Death, He Returned One Last Time.
headline.print_headline: Lewis’s Funeral Procession Follows His Footsteps Across Bridge

docs.lead_paragraph: As Americans debate how far the country should go to make amends for slavery and other racial injustices, a conversation reawakened by the killing of George Floyd, a city in North Carolina has taken the first step: It approved reparations for Black residents.

headline.main: North Carolina City Approves Reparations for Black Residents
headline.print_headline: Southern City Votes to Make Reparations Over Racism

docs.abstract: In a state with a brutal racist history, the Black Lives Matter protests in Portland, Ore., have been overwhelmingly attended by white demonstrators.
docs.snippet: In a state with a brutal racist history, the Black Lives Matter protests in Portland, Ore., have been overwhelmingly attended by white demonstrators.
docs.lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — Seyi Fasoranti, a chemist who moved to Oregon from the East Coast six months ago, has watched the Black Lives Matter protests in Portland with fascination. A sea of white faces in one of the whitest major American cities has cried out for racial justice every night for nearly two months.

headline.main: How One of America’s Whitest Cities Became the Center of B.L.M. Protests
headline.print_headline: Marching for Black Lives in the Whitest Big City
